---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About AcuMaven — Steve Milner, Acumatica Consultant"
  description="Steve Milner is an Acumatica ERP specialist with 11 active certifications, 20+ implementations, and a focus on field service, construction, and manufacturing companies."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>The Consultant Who Actually Does the Work</h1>
      <p>Boutique means something. At AcuMaven, the person who closes the deal is the person who shows up on day one — and every day after.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio + Headshot -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="headshot-placeholder">
          <span style="font-size: 3rem;">👤</span>
          <p>Steve Milner<br/>Photo coming soon</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Steve Milner</h2>
          <p class="section-sub">Founder, AcuMaven Inc — San Clemente, CA</p>
          <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Steve is an ex-military professional with 20+ years in business software — and has been an Acumatica specialist long enough to have seen everything go wrong at least once, and fixed most of it.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">He founded AcuMaven as a deliberately boutique practice: no layers of account managers, no junior consultants doing the work while a senior collects credit. When you hire AcuMaven, you get Steve. On every call, in every configuration session, at every go-live.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">He specializes in field service companies — HVAC, plumbing, electrical, construction — industries where ERP failure is measured in stalled dispatches, lost jobs, and angry technicians. He knows the edge cases. He's fixed the broken ones.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--muted);">He's also developing AcuLens — an AI copilot for field service technicians built on Meta smart glasses, because he thinks the ERP-to-field gap is still wide open and worth closing. <a href="/aculens">Learn more →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Certifications -->
  <section style="background: var(--light);">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Active Acumatica Certifications</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">11 certifications across implementation, development, and module depth. Not a generalist with a partner badge.</p>
      <div class="cert-grid">
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Construction Business Consultant</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Business Consultant</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Case Management</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Inventory &amp; Order Management</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Fixed Assets</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ REST API Integration Developer</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Implementation Project Manager</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ OData Integration Developer</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Project Accounting</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Technical Specialist</div>
        <div class="cert-item">✓ Official Celigo Partner</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why AcuMaven -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why AcuMaven</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">What a boutique firm actually means in practice.</p>
      <div class="why-grid">
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>Steve is your consultant</h3>
          <p>Not a project manager. Not a junior assigned after the sales call. Steve scopes it, configures it, trains on it, and supports it. There's no one between you and the person doing the work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>Field service is the specialty</h3>
          <p>Dispatch, service orders, mobile technicians, job costing, field billing — these aren't features to us. They're the entire focus. We know this vertical better than generalist partners with 12 industries in their deck.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>We take the hard projects</h3>
          <p>Rescue projects. Failed go-lives. Implementations someone else walked away from. Most partners won't touch them. We built a practice around fixing them and we're good at it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>Honest answers, not sales pitches</h3>
          <p>If Acumatica isn't the right fit for your company, Steve will tell you. If your current system can be fixed without a full replacement, he'll tell you that too. The goal is the right outcome — not the biggest engagement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to talk to the actual consultant?</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">No pre-sales process. Just a straight conversation about what you need.</p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary" style="font-size: 1.05rem; padding: 0.9rem 2.25rem;">Talk to Steve</a>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted);">Or email directly: <a href="mailto:steve@acumaveninc.com">steve@acumaveninc.com</a> · (949) 257-7031</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
